ase-01-project-skeleton-resources\",\n3819:       \"targetCapabilitySearch\": [\n3820:         \"Cangjie SDK declarations confirm direct resource support in pure Cangjie: `ohos.base.ResourceStr` (`C:\\\\Users\\\\Sieger\\\\.cangjie-sdk\\\\6.0\\\\cangjie\\\\api\\\\modules\\\\linux_ohos_aarch64_cjnative\\\\ohos\\\\ohos.base.cj.d:618-626`), `ohos.resource.AppResource` (`...\\\\ohos.resource.cj.d:20-97`), and `ohos.resource_manager.ResourceManager` formatted string APIs including `getString`, `getStringByName`, `getPluralStringByName`, and numeric lookups (`...\\\\ohos.resource_manager.cj.d:20-199`).\",\n3821:         \"HarmonyOS Cangjie docs confirm `ohos.resource` is a Cangjie-callable LocalizationKit module imported via `import kit.LocalizationKit.*`, and `AppResource` carries bundle/module/id plus formatting params for resource lookup (`D:\\\\workspace\\\\Foodike\\\\.agents\\\\skills\\\\cangjie-harmonyos-doc-search\\\\harmonyos-6.1-8k\\\\API\\\\LocalizationKit\\\\cj-apis-resource\\\\cj-apis-resource.md:9-153`).\",\n3822:         \"HarmonyOS resource guidance confirms the standard HarmonyOS resource-category and access path should be used for multi-language and multi-device adaptation rather than custom fallback handling (`D:\\\\workspace\\\\Foodike\\\\.agents\\\\skills\\\\cangjie-harmonyos-doc-search\\\\harmonyos-6.1-8k\\\\Guide\\\\cj-start\\\\start\\\\cj-ide-resource-categories-and-access\\\\资源分类与访问\\\\.abstract.md:1`).\"\n3823:       ],\n3824:       \"targetApiOrLibrary\": \"HarmonyOS Cangjie LocalizationKit resource model (`ohos.base.ResourceStr`, `ohos.resource.AppResource`, `ohos.resource_manager.ResourceManager`) with standard HarmonyOS `string.json`/`color.json` resources\",\n3825:       \"targetStrategy\": \"Phase 01 should migrate Android strings/colors/themes/media into HarmonyOS resource files and keep user-visible labels resource-backed. Use `ResourceStr`/`AppResource` directly in ArkUI component props where supported, and use `ResourceManager.getString(...)` / `getStringByName(...)` for formatted or named retrieval instead of hard-coded strings or local fallback tables.\",\n3826:       \"targetEndpoints\": [\n3827:         \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/app_router.cj\",\n3828:         \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/common/foodike_resources.cj\",\n3829:         \"entry/src/main/resources/base/element/string.json\",\n3830:         \"entry/src/main/resources/base/element/color.json\"\n3831:       ],\n3832:       \"tests\": [\n3833:         \"string key coverage check\",\n3834:         \"placeholder preservation check\",\n3835:         \"locale selection smoke test\"\n3836:       ],\n3837:       \"sdkDeclarationEvidence\": [\n3838:         \"`ohos.base.ResourceStr` is a direct SDK interface and `String` extends it (`C:\\\\Users\\\\Sieger\\\\.cangjie-sdk\\\\6.0\\\\cangjie\\\\api\\\\modules\\\\linux_ohos_aarch64_cjnative\\\\ohos\\\\ohos.base.cj.d:618-626`).\",\n3839:         \"`ohos.resource.AppResource` directly implements `ResourceStr` and carries `params` for formatted resource usage (`C:\\\\Users\\\\Sieger\\\\.cangjie-sdk\\\\6.0\\\\cangjie\\\\api\\\\modules\\\\linux_ohos_aarch64_cjnative\\\\ohos\\\\ohos.resource.cj.d:20-97`).\",\n3840:         \"`ohos.resource_manager.ResourceManager` exposes direct Cangjie string/number/plural retrieval APIs including formatted lookups (`C:\\\\Users\\\\Sieger\\\\.cangjie-sdk\\\\6.0\\\\cangjie\\\\api\\\\modules\\\\linux_ohos_aarch64_cjnative\\\\ohos\\\\ohos.resource_manager.cj.d:20-199`).\",\n3841:         \"ArkUI components consume resource-backed values directly, for example `Text.init(content: ?ResourceStr, ...)` (`C:\\\\Users\\\\Sieger\\\\.cangjie-sdk\\\\6.0\\\\cangjie\\\\api\\\\modules\\\\linux_ohos_aarch64_cjnative\\\\ohos\\\\ohos.arkui.component.text.cj.d:47-59`) and `Button.init(label: ResourceStr)` (`C:\\\\Users\\\\Sieger\\\\.cangjie-sdk\\\\6.0\\\\cangjie\\\\api\\\\modules\\\\linux_ohos_aarch64_cjnative\\\\ohos\\\\ohos.arkui.component.button.cj.d:306-314`).\"\n3842:       ],\n3843:       \"cangjieCallableEvidence\": [\n3844:         \"LocalizationKit documentation defines `ohos.resource` as a Cangjie module imported with `import kit.LocalizationKit.*`, with `AppResource` available to Cangjie code (`D:\\\\workspace\\\\Foodike\\\\.agents\\\\skills\\\\cangjie-harmonyos-doc-search\\\\harmonyos-6.1-8k\\\\API\\\\LocalizationKit\\\\cj-apis-resource\\\\cj-apis-resource.md:9-153`).\",\n3845:         \"The installed SDK declarations plus ArkUI `ResourceStr` component signatures provide a direct Cangjie-callable path for localized labels and formatted resources without introducing an ArkTS bridge.\"\n3846:       ],\n3847:       \"discoveryOnlyEvidence\": [],\n3848:       \"compileProbeEvidence\": [],\n3849:       \"preResolutionDecision\": \"resolved-real-api\",\n3850:       \"phaseCapabilityResolution\": \"resolved-real-api\",\n3851:       \"blocker\": \"\",\n3852:       \"targetFallback\": \"\",\n3853:       \"futureCompletionPath\": \"\",\n3854:       \"notes\": \"Direct Cangjie resource APIs exist, so this capability must be implemented in phase 01 through real HarmonyOS resource files and resource-backed UI text. No package lookup or bridge is needed for this phase capability.\",\n3855:       \"capabilityFacts\": {\n3856:         \"schemaVersion\": 1,\n3857:         \"resolutionKind\": \"direct-api\",\n3858:         \"activeFallback\": {\n3859:           \"used\": false,\n3860:           \"fallbackKind\": \"\",\n3861:           \"reason\": \"\",\n3862:           \"blocker\": \"\"\n3863:         },\n3864:         \"apiEvidence\": [\n3865:           {\n3866:             \"kind\": \"cangjie-sdk-declaration\",\n3867:             \"detail\": \"`ohos.base.ResourceStr` plus `String <: ResourceStr` in `ohos.base.cj.d:618-626`.\"\n3868:           },\n3869:           {\n3870:             \"kind\": \"cangjie-sdk-declaration\",\n3871:             \"detail\": \"`ohos.resource.AppResource <: Length & ResourceColor & R